I live nearby and the burning cooking fumes coming from their restaurant pollute my entire home all day everyday.  It smells awful! Much like burnt cooking oil all day long! I can only imagine how unhealthy this is to the environment + people's health! I don't even open my windows for fresh air circulation throughout the day until sometime after 2am when they close their restaurant. I hope they put a stop to their pollution before DEP does!!!

Since I live 10 minutes away this used to be my favorite go-to restaurant. The food was always amazing and the service was really nice. The reason why I gave it a two stars is because recently the food has been extremely spicy and salty and I always get "mildly spicy." I even told them it was inedible but they just added vegetables to try to balance it. In addition the two nice waitresses are gone! I'm kind of upset and I don't think I'll go back until they fix this issue.

There was a pile on my plate from picking them out. The items u choose to go with the noodles are barely there. I chose squid and fish balls but I only found like 4 small pieces of them while theres a ton of mushrooms and other stuff. The only thing good was the fry pan thing where you can pick what you want to cook in a wok.

Szechuan style food. Its sort of like the places in Flushing where you can pick your own meat/vegetables and they will fry it using their special Szechuan spices. Overall portion is good for a date. Taste is solid like the ones in Flushing, you are able to choose the level of the spiciness.
